rminal.png" class="kg-image" alt="FOSS Weekly #23.44: Kernel 6.6, Midori Reborn, Gaming Distros, Arch Install and More" loading="lazy" width="920" height="675" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/10/6-scroll-lines-terminal.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/10/6-scroll-lines-terminal.png 920w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"></figure><hr><h2 id="%F0%9F%A4%A3-meme-of-the-week"> 🤣 Meme of the week</h2><p> Be careful, young padawan, enemies lurk everywhere. </p><figure class="kg-card kg-image-card"><img src="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/10/meme26.png" class="kg-image" alt="FOSS Weekly #23.44: Kernel 6.6, Midori Reborn, Gaming Distros, Arch Install and More" loading="lazy" width="1080" height="1080" srcset="https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w600/2023/10/meme26.png 600w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/size/w1000/2023/10/meme26.png 1000w, https://itsfoss.com/content/images/2023/10/meme26.png 1080w" sizes="(min-width: 720px) 720px"></figure><hr><h2 id="%F0%9F%97%93%EF%B8%8F-tech-trivia"> 🗓️ Tech Trivia</h2><p> Vim was first released on 2nd November 1991. Initially, Vim was an acronym for Vi IMitation but later it was changed to Vi IMproved.</p><p> Inkscape was also released on 2nd November 2003 for the first time.</p><hr><h2 id="%F0%9F%A7%91%E2%80%8D%F0%9F%A4%9D%E2%80%8D%F0%9F%A7%91-fossverse-corner"> 🧑‍🤝‍🧑 FOSSverse corner</h2><p> The FOSSverse is up and about with discussions about <strong>Ubuntu&#39;s upcoming LTS release</strong> that has been code-named “ <strong>Noble Numbat</strong> ”.</p><figure class="kg-card kg-bookmark-card"> <a class="kg-bookmark-container" href="https://itsfoss.community/t/ubuntu-24-04-noble-numbat/11379?ref=itsfoss.com"><div class="kg-bookmark-content"><div class="kg-bookmark-title">Ubuntu 24.04 &#39;Noble Numbat&#39;</div> <div class="kg-bookmark-description">I see they opened the next release up for development and announced the name. Does this mean more of our Australian members wi